nobel-chemistry-1904 | 1904 Sir William Ramsay | http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/chemistry/laureates/1904/ | winner:Sir William Ramsay description:in recognition of his services in the discovery of the inert gaseous elements in air, and his determination of their place in the periodic system
nobel-chemistry-1903 | 1903 Svante August Arrhenius | http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/chemistry/laureates/1903/ | winner:Svante August Arrhenius description:in recognition of the extraordinary services he has rendered to the advancement of chemistry by his electrolytic theory of dissociation
nobel-chemistry-1902 | 1902 Hermann Emil Fischer | http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/chemistry/laureates/1902/ | winner:Hermann Emil Fischer description:in recognition of the extraordinary services he has rendered by his work on sugar and purine syntheses
nobel-chemistry-1901 | 1901 Jacobus Henricus van 't Hoff | http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/chemistry/laureates/1901/ | winner:Jacobus Henricus van 't Hoff description:in recognition of the extraordinary services he has rendered by the discovery of the laws of chemical dynamics and osmotic pressure in solutions
